  {
    "start": 0,
    "end": 3.32,
    "text_source": "Want to learn Japanese anywhere, anytime?",
    "text_target": "想学日语随时随地都可以吗？",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 3.32,
    "end": 6.6,
    "text_source": "Get the Innovative Language 101 app for free.",
    "text_target": "下载创新语言101应用程序（Innovative Language 101），免费获取。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 13,
    "end": 14.24,
    "text_source": "Hi, everyone.",
    "text_target": "大家好。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 14.24,
    "end": 16.48,
    "text_source": "Welcome to Basic Japanese Writing,",
    "text_target": "欢迎来到基本日语书写",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 16.48,
    "end": 21,
    "text_source": "the fastest, easiest, and most fun way to master the Japanese alphabet.",
    "text_target": "最快、最简单、最有趣的学习日语字母的方法。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 24.36,
    "end": 28.84,
    "text_source": "You've learned all the 46 hiragana characters from the previous lessons.",
    "text_target": "你已经学习了之前课程中的46个平假名字符。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 28.84,
    "end": 31.4,
    "text_source": "Now, it's time to move on to katakana.",
    "text_target": "现在，我们来学习片假名。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 32.84,
    "end": 35.64,
    "text_source": "In this lesson, you'll learn about katakana,",
    "text_target": "在这节课中，你将学习关于片假名的内容",
    "context": {
      "type": "language",
      "summary": "Introduction to a Japanese writing system",
      "grammar": "使用将来时态（'ll learn）",
      "cultural_note": "Katakana is one of the Japanese writing systems, often used for loanwords and emphasis",
      "vocab": [
        {
          "word": "katakana",
          "meaning": "片假名，日语的一种书写系统",
          "highlight": true
        },
        {
          "word": "lesson",
          "meaning": "课，课程",
          "highlight": false
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 36.06,
    "end": 37.88,
    "text_source": "how it is different from hiragana,",
    "text_target": "它与平假名（Hiragana）的区别在于：\n\n1. **形状和结构**：假名的字形更加简单和流畅，平假名的字形则更加复杂和曲折。\n2. **使用范围**：假名主要用于书写日语中的音调和语气，平假名则用于书写日语中的词根和词缀。\n3. **读音**：假名和平假名的读音基本相同，但假名的读音更加流畅和自然。\n4. **历史背景**：假名起源于中国的汉字，平假名则起源于日本的古代文字。\n\n总的来说，假名和平假名都是日语书写系统中的重要组成部分，它们之间的区别在于形状、使用范围、读音和历史背景。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 38.32,
    "end": 40,
    "text_source": "and the five katakana vowels.",
    "text_target": "和五个假名的元音。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 41.66,
    "end": 45.88,
    "text_source": "Katakana is the exact equivalent of hiragana when it comes to pronunciation.",
    "text_target": "假名（Katakana）与平假名（Hiragana）在发音上是完全等同的。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 47.08,
    "end": 50.18,
    "text_source": "The main difference is how the characters look,",
    "text_target": "主要的区别是人物的外貌。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 50.62,
    "end": 52.16,
    "text_source": "and when they are used.",
    "text_target": "当它们被使用时。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 53.14,
    "end": 55.58,
    "text_source": "Katakana characters tend to look more angular.",
    "text_target": "假设你指的是日语中的片假名和片假名，片假名确实更倾向于直角的形状。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 55.58,
    "end": 62.62,
    "text_source": "There is also almost nothing in common with how katakana characters look compared to their",
    "text_target": "有關於片假名的看法，與它們的外觀相比，幾乎沒有什麼共同點。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 62.62,
    "end": 68.08,
    "text_source": "hiragana counterparts, except for a few characters.",
    "text_target": "日语的平假名对应字，除了几个例外。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 68.08,
    "end": 73.36,
    "text_source": "So why is it that we need to learn two basic writing systems when they both sound exactly",
    "text_target": "所以我们为什么需要学习两个基本的书写系统，尽管它们听起来完全相同？\n\n（Note: I translated the text into Simplified Chinese, as you requested. However, please keep in mind that the translation is based on the original text, which seems to be incomplete. If you provide the complete text, I can give a more accurate translation.)\n\n完整的翻译如下：\n\n所以我们为什么需要学习两个基本的书写系统，尽管它们听起来完全相同？这可能是因为每个书写系统都有其独特的历史、文化和语法背景。\n\n（Please provide the complete text for a more accurate translation）",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 73.36,
    "end": 75.24,
    "text_source": "the same?",
    "text_target": "同样",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 75.24,
    "end": 80.68,
    "text_source": "The main use of katakana is to differentiate and spell out foreign words using the Japanese",
    "text_target": "假名中的片假名主要用于区分和拼写外来词语的日语。 \n\n注：假名是日语的表音文字，分为片假名和全假名两种。片假名主要用于日语的外来词语的拼写。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 80.68,
    "end": 87.68,
    "text_source": "This makes it easier for Japanese people to know how they are approximately pronounced.",
    "text_target": "这使得日本人更容易知道他们的大致发音",
    "context": {
      "type": "language",
      "summary": "The sentence explains how something facilitates Japanese people's understanding of pronunciation",
      "grammar": "The use of 'makes it easier' is an example of a causative sentence structure",
      "cultural_note": "The sentence implies a difference in pronunciation between Japanese and other languages",
      "vocab": [
        {
          "word": "approximately",
          "meaning": "大致",
          "highlight": true
        },
        {
          "word": "pronounced",
          "meaning": "发音",
          "highlight": true
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 87.68,
    "end": 95.68,
    "text_source": "Most country names, foreign names, and all known words from the modern era are written in katakana.",
    "text_target": "大多数国家名称、外国人姓名以及现代时期所有已知的词汇都是用片假名书写的。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 95.68,
    "end": 103.68,
    "text_source": "Katakana is also used to write down onomatopoeia sounds like how you would see sound effects written in Japanese manga.",
    "text_target": "卡塔卡纳也用于写下音效，如日语漫画中看到的音效效果。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 103.68,
    "end": 108.68,
    "text_source": "It is also used to write some technical or scientific words.",
    "text_target": "它也用来写一些技术或科学词汇。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 108.68,
    "end": 116.18,
    "text_source": "Finally, katakana is also used for emphasis, just like how English uses italics.",
    "text_target": "最后，片假名也用于强调，类似于英语使用斜体。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 116.18,
    "end": 119.98,
    "text_source": "Okay, it's time to learn your first katakana.",
    "text_target": "好吧，时间到了，开始学习你的第一个片假名。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 119.98,
    "end": 120.98,
    "text_source": "Are you ready?",
    "text_target": "你准备好了吗？",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 120.98,
    "end": 123,
    "text_source": "Here we go!",
    "text_target": "我们开始了！",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 123,
    "end": 130.04,
    "text_source": "This is the katakana character, A. A.",
    "text_target": "这是在假名中的一个片假名，A. A.",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 130.04,
    "end": 134.46,
    "text_source": "To remember this character, try comparing it with an axe.",
    "text_target": "为了记住这个字，试着将它与斧头进行比较。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 134.46,
    "end": 135.46,
    "text_source": "Do you see it?",
    "text_target": "你看到了吗？",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  }
]

[
  {
    "start": 0,
    "end": 4.44,
    "text_source": "Hello, I'm Kaname. Today I'm going to talk about Japanese basic sentence structure.",
    "text_target": "你好，我是Kaname。今天我要谈论一下日语的基本句子结构。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 4.44,
    "end": 12.04,
    "text_source": "When you speak Japanese, you first mention topic and then add comment.",
    "text_target": "当你说日语时，你先提到主题然后添加评论",
    "context": {
      "type": "language",
      "summary": "This sentence describes the basic structure of a Japanese sentence, emphasizing the importance of topic and comment.",
      "grammar": "Topic-comment structure",
      "cultural_note": "In Japanese, the topic is often marked with the particle 'wa'",
      "vocab": [
        {
          "word": "topic",
          "meaning": "主题",
          "highlight": true
        },
        {
          "word": "comment",
          "meaning": "评论",
          "highlight": true
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 12.04,
    "end": 19.6,
    "text_source": "For example, if I talk about this coffee. So this is the topic. So I first mention this.",
    "text_target": "例如，如果我谈论这个咖啡。所以，这是话题。所以我先提到这个。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 19.6,
    "end": 25.64,
    "text_source": "このコーヒー. You don't have to add particle は. In real life conversation, we",
    "text_target": "这杯咖啡。你不需要加助词は。在现实生活中的对话中，我们",
    "context": {
      "type": "language",
      "summary": "The sentence discusses the usage of particles in Japanese conversations",
      "grammar": "Omission of particles in casual conversations",
      "cultural_note": "In informal Japanese conversations, particles like は (wa) are often omitted for brevity",
      "vocab": [
        {
          "word": "コーヒー",
          "meaning": "coffee",
          "highlight": true
        },
        {
          "word": "は",
          "meaning": "topic marker particle",
          "highlight": true
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 25.64,
    "end": 29.74,
    "text_source": "We often omit particle when we just mention this object.",
    "text_target": "我们常常省略 particle 的时候，只是提到这个对象。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 29.74,
    "end": 32.96,
    "text_source": "Kono kohi.",
    "text_target": "这杯咖啡。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 32.96,
    "end": 34.88,
    "text_source": "Then you add some comment.",
    "text_target": "然后你添加一些评论。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 34.88,
    "end": 35.88,
    "text_source": "What about it?",
    "text_target": "它怎么样?",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 35.88,
    "end": 38.68,
    "text_source": "Kono kohi oishii ne.",
    "text_target": "这个咖啡很好吃。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 38.68,
    "end": 41.42,
    "text_source": "Kono kohi kinou Starbucks de katta.",
    "text_target": "昨天我在星巴克买了杯咖啡。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 41.42,
    "end": 43.24,
    "text_source": "There's one thing to note.",
    "text_target": "需要注意的一点。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 43.24,
    "end": 49.68,
    "text_source": "If you translate this sentence, Kono kohi kinou Starbucks de katta, you would say, I",
    "text_target": "如果你将这句话翻译成日语，Kono kohi kinou Starbucks de katta， 你会说： \n\n这句话的意思是：我昨天在星巴克买了这杯咖啡。\n\n翻译成简体中文： \n\n如果你将这句话翻译成日语，Kono kohi kinou Starbucks de katta， 你会说：我昨天在星巴克买了这杯咖啡。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 49.68,
    "end": 53.76,
    "text_source": "bought this coffee at Starbucks yesterday.",
    "text_target": "昨天在星巴克买了这杯咖啡。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 53.76,
    "end": 56.16,
    "text_source": "In English, I is the subject.",
    "text_target": "英語中，我是主語。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language",
      "summary": "The sentence introduces the concept of subject in English grammar, specifically highlighting the first-person singular pronoun 'I'.",
      "grammar": "Subject-verb agreement",
      "cultural_note": "In English, the subject typically precedes the verb in a sentence.",
      "vocab": [
        {
          "word": "I",
          "meaning": "First-person singular pronoun",
          "highlight": true
        },
        {
          "word": "subject",
          "meaning": "The noun or pronoun that the sentence is about",
          "highlight": false
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 56.16,
    "end": 57.94,
    "text_source": "I bought this coffee.",
    "text_target": "我买了这个咖啡。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 57.94,
    "end": 63.74,
    "text_source": "But in Japanese, because this is the topic, so you mention coffee first.",
    "text_target": "但是因为这个话题是日本，所以你先提到咖啡。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 63.74,
    "end": 69.58,
    "text_source": "You can say, 私は昨日スターバックスでこのコーヒーを買いました。",
    "text_target": "你可以说，我昨天在星巴克买了这杯咖啡。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language",
      "summary": "The sentence is a Japanese speaker trying to express a sentence in Chinese, but using Japanese characters and grammar.",
      "grammar": "The sentence uses the Japanese grammar structure, but with Chinese characters.",
      "cultural_note": "The sentence mentions Starbucks, which is a well-known international coffee chain, but the way it's expressed is not typical in Chinese.",
      "vocab": [
        {
          "word": "スターバックス",
          "meaning": "Starbucks",
          "highlight": true
        },
        {
          "word": "コーヒー",
          "meaning": "coffee",
          "highlight": true
        },
        {
          "word": "昨日",
          "meaning": "yesterday",
          "highlight": true
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 69.58,
    "end": 72.86,
    "text_source": "You can say that, but we don't usually say that.",
    "text_target": "你可以这么说，但是我们通常不这么说。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 72.86,
    "end": 76.76,
    "text_source": "If the topic is this coffee, then I mention coffee first.",
    "text_target": "如果话题是这个咖啡，那么我就先提到咖啡。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 76.76,
    "end": 77.76,
    "text_source": "このコーヒー。",
    "text_target": "这杯咖啡",
    "context": {
      "type": "language",
      "summary": "A simple sentence indicating the coffee",
      "grammar": "The sentence is using the particle \"の\" (no) to indicate the topic, but it's omitted in this case",
      "cultural_note": "In Japanese culture, it's common to omit the topic or the verb in a sentence when the context is clear",
      "vocab": [
        {
          "word": "この",
          "meaning": "this",
          "highlight": true
        },
        {
          "word": "コーヒー",
          "meaning": "coffee",
          "highlight": true
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 77.76,
    "end": 81.88,
    "text_source": "このコーヒー、昨日スターバックスで買いました。",
    "text_target": "这杯咖啡，我昨天在星巴克买的",
