    "text_target": "和五个假名元音。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 41.66,
    "end": 45.88,
    "text_source": "Katakana is the exact equivalent of hiragana when it comes to pronunciation.",
    "text_target": "片假名与平假名在发音上是完全等同的。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 47.08,
    "end": 50.18,
    "text_source": "The main difference is how the characters look,",
    "text_target": "主要的区别是角色外貌的不同。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 50.62,
    "end": 52.16,
    "text_source": "and when they are used.",
    "text_target": "当它们被使用时。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 53.14,
    "end": 55.58,
    "text_source": "Katakana characters tend to look more angular.",
    "text_target": "假日语的片假名字符倾向于看起来更锐利。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 55.58,
    "end": 62.62,
    "text_source": "There is also almost nothing in common with how katakana characters look compared to their",
    "text_target": "有一个类似的例子是日语的片假名和平假名。 \n\n在这个例子中，片假名和平假名的外观几乎没有共同点。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 62.62,
    "end": 68.08,
    "text_source": "hiragana counterparts, except for a few characters.",
    "text_target": "假日格拉纳对应的平假名，除了几个例外。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 68.08,
    "end": 73.36,
    "text_source": "So why is it that we need to learn two basic writing systems when they both sound exactly",
    "text_target": "So 为什么我们需要学习两个基本的书写系统，尽管它们听起来完全相同？\n\n或\n\n我们为什么需要学习两个基本的书写系统，尽管它们听起来完全相同？\n\n或\n\n为什么我们需要学习两个基本的书写系统，尽管它们听起来完全相同？\n\n(注意：上述翻译有多种可能的表达方式，具体取决于你想要表达的意思和语气。)\n\n如果你想提供更多上下文信息，我可以尝试给出更准确的翻译。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 73.36,
    "end": 75.24,
    "text_source": "the same?",
    "text_target": "相同",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 75.24,
    "end": 80.68,
    "text_source": "The main use of katakana is to differentiate and spell out foreign words using the Japanese",
    "text_target": "假名中的片假名主要用于区分和拼写外来词语，特别是使用日语写作外国词语时。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 80.68,
    "end": 87.68,
    "text_source": "This makes it easier for Japanese people to know how they are approximately pronounced.",
    "text_target": "这使得日本人更容易知道他们的大致发音",
    "context": {
      "type": "language",
      "summary": "The sentence explains how something facilitates Japanese people's understanding of pronunciation",
      "grammar": "The use of 'approximately' indicates an estimation or rough idea",
      "cultural_note": "In Japanese culture, pronunciation is crucial for effective communication",
      "vocab": [
        {
          "word": "approximately",
          "meaning": "大致，约",
          "highlight": true
        },
        {
          "word": "pronounced",
          "meaning": "发音",
          "highlight": true
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 87.68,
    "end": 95.68,
    "text_source": "Most country names, foreign names, and all known words from the modern era are written in katakana.",
    "text_target": "大多数国家名称、外国人姓名以及现代时期所知的所有词语都是用片假名写的。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 95.68,
    "end": 103.68,
    "text_source": "Katakana is also used to write down onomatopoeia sounds like how you would see sound effects written in Japanese manga.",
    "text_target": "卡塔卡纳也用于写下噪音词语，如在日本漫画中看到的声效写法。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 103.68,
    "end": 108.68,
    "text_source": "It is also used to write some technical or scientific words.",
    "text_target": "它也用来写一些技术或科学词汇。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 108.68,
    "end": 116.18,
    "text_source": "Finally, katakana is also used for emphasis, just like how English uses italics.",
    "text_target": "最后，片假名也用于强调，类似于英语中的斜体。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 116.18,
    "end": 119.98,
    "text_source": "Okay, it's time to learn your first katakana.",
    "text_target": "好吧，时间到了，学习你的第一个片假名。",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 119.98,
    "end": 120.98,
    "text_source": "Are you ready?",
    "text_target": "你准备好了吗？",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 120.98,
    "end": 123,
    "text_source": "Here we go!",
    "text_target": "我们开始了！",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 123,
    "end": 130.04,
    "text_source": "This is the katakana character, A. A.",
    "text_target": "这是片假名的A. A.",
    "context": {
      "type": "language"
    }
  },
  {
    "start": 130.04,
    "end": 134.46,
    "text_source": "To remember this character, try comparing it with an axe.",
    "text_target": "为了记住这个字，试着将其与斧头进行比较。",
